                <h2 class="txt-black">The Maverick Awards Categories</h2>
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">1. The Maverick Start Up of The Year Award</p>
                <p>This award category is designed to recognise and honour the 'rising star' young entrepreneurs across all sectors whose enterprises have been in operation for a minimum period of 1 year and not longer than 3 years, turning over a minimum of R1million per annum, with no maximum threshold on their turnover. Entrepreneurs entering this category are NOT ELIGIBLE to enter the other award categories below due to the 3 year minimum operational period required for all other categories.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">2. The Maverick Award for Employment Creation</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning in excess of R3million revenue per year, employing a minimum of 20 employees. And while they have created a significant number of jobs they must also display a significant investment and dedication towards the uplifting, up-skilling and training of their employees.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">3. The Maverick Without Borders Award for Export Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue per year, primarily operating in South Africa, however they have must have successfully established distribution of their products/services in foreign markets such that a significant proportion of their revenue comes from foreign markets. </p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">4. The Maverick Award for Social Innovation Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young social entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more turning a minimum of R3million revenue/grants/donations per year, they must clearly demonstrate novel, ground-breaking and innovative methodologies in their development &amp; deployment of solutions that address social issues in South Africa.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">5. The Maverick Award for Service Innovation Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young service based entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while clearly having developed and deployed novel, ground-breaking and innovative methodologies of delivering a service in any sector of the economy to their customers in a manner that clearly displays a marked improvement in user experience or value derived thereof.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">6. The Maverick Award for Manufacturing and Industrial Innovation Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while having developed and deployed novel, ground-breaking and innovative methodologies in the manufacturing and industrial sectors of the economy in a manner that clearly displays a marked improvement in production efficiencies, production quality or product user experiences.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">7. The Maverick Award for Built Environment Innovation Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while having developed and deployed novel, ground-breaking and innovative methodologies in the built-environment sectors of the economy - Construction, Architecture, Quantity Surveying, Civil, Mechanical, Electrical Engineering and Draughtsmen just to mention a few.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">8. The Maverick Award for Agricultural Innovation Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while having developed and deployed novel, ground-breaking and innovative methodologies in the agricultural  sectors of the economy - Crop and Livestock Farming, Agro-Processing, Agro-Value Chain Products/Services  and  Processed Agro-Distribution and other related sectors.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">9. The Maverick Award for Green Innovation Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while having developed and deployed novel and ground-breaking innovations in the green sectors of the economy such as renewable &amp; alternative energy, environmental conservation, energy conservation and other related sectors.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">10. The Maverick Award for Technology Innovation Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while having developed and deployed novel and ground-breaking innovations of a technological nature across all industries and sectors.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">11. The Maverick Award for Blue Ocean Innovation Excellence</p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while having developed and deployed novel and ground-breaking innovations of such great proportions that have never been witnessed before within a known industry or market space, such that a completely new, previously unknown and uncontested market space is created through this new disruptive business model, method(s) or invention(s).</p><br /><br />
                <p class="sub-prof-head txt-black">The Coveted Maverick Award Category</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold">1.	The Maverick of the Year Award for South Africa's Best Young Entrepreneur</p>
                <p>This is the most coveted award category to be won at The Maverick Awards by the best young entrepreneur(s). This category is NOT OPEN FOR ENTRY; it will be decided upon by our judges and selected from the winners of the main categories above EXCEPT The Maverick Start-Up of The Year Award.</p>
